Uses of Class
com.cisco.mscviewer.model.MSCDataModel

  • Packages that use MSCDataModel 
    Package Description
    com.cisco.mscviewer
    Contains classes and packages for MSCViewer, a tool for visualization and analysis of sequence diagram charts (see Wikipedia}.
    com.cisco.mscviewer.graph
    Contains classes for creation of a graph used to compute a topological sorting of Event in the data model.
    com.cisco.mscviewer.gui
    Contains classes for the GUI of MSCViewer.
    com.cisco.mscviewer.io
    Contains classes for loading/saving MSCViewer data model from and to files.
    com.cisco.mscviewer.model
    Contains classes representing MSCViewer view and data model.

    • Uses of MSCDataModel in com.cisco.mscviewer.graph

      Constructors in com.cisco.mscviewer.graph with parameters of type MSCDataModel 
      Constructor and Description
      Graph(MSCDataModel dm)
      creates a graph where: Each node represents a sequence of events with same timestamp and entity there is an edge between each pair of consecutive (by timestamp) nodes for the same entity there is an edge between each pair of consecutive (by timestamp) nodes not belonging to the same entity and with different timestamp note: this code assumes that all events belonging to the same entity and with the same timestamp are going to appear contiguously in the global array of events in the datamodel.
